---
alwaysApply: true
---

- Before you start planning, you can have a look at the `README.md` file inside of project so you can have a brief picture of functionality it already has. It also includes links to different libraries used in project
- After finishing a task, run a smoke test in a browser using playwright. Find more information inside [smoke-test-handoff.mdc](./smoke-test-handoff.mdc)
- After finishing a task, run unit tests with React Three Fiber Test Renderer (RTTR) via `npm run test:unit`
- After creating a new feature for the project, don't forget to document only important information about it in `README.md` file. Include only features, not bugfixes or "best practices" info. Make it concise and short.
